nning Claude Code from GitHub Actions with cross-run session continuity. Validated end-to-end in this repo on 2026-05-07 via `.github/workflows/poc-session.yml` and the `temp/poc/POC-2/` artefacts.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:18:1. The Claude Code session state directory `~/.claude/projects/`. Cached per ticket using `actions/cache`.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:19:2. The Claude Code session ID. Committed in `state.json` so the next run can pass it to `--resume`.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:24:  state.json       last_session_id, run_count, last_kind, last_run_at\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:25:  transcript.md    one section per run with prompt, response, session ids\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:67:│  outputs: session_id, execution_file        │\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:73:│  - read action's session_id output          │\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:101:- Does **not** expose the `session_id` output.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:114:- `session_id` — UUID. Pass to `--resume` next run.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:115:- `execution_file` — path on the runner to a JSON file with the full conversation. Always present even when `session_id` is empty (older actions, fallback case).\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:124:- Save key: `claude-session-<TICKET-ID>-<github.run_id>` (unique per run, so `actions/cache/save@v4` does not error on duplicate-key).\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:126:- Restore-keys (prefix list): `claude-session-<TICKET-ID>-`. This is what actually matches on the second run, since the run id changes.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:131:- After eviction, `--resume <id>` will fail at the CLI level because the prior session transcripts are gone from disk.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:132:- Mitigation: even if Claude cannot resume, the run can rebuild context from `state.json` and `transcript.md` and start a fresh session. Always pass plan.md/spec.md/transcript.md content into the prompt, and treat `--resume` as a best-effort acceleration.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:138:- New session: action emits a UUID.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:141:Documented behavior elsewhere claims session ID can rotate on resume. Defensive handling:\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:143:- After every run, always update `state.json` with the freshly emitted `session_id`, regardless of whether it equals the prior id.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:144:- Treat session ID as opaque.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:145:- If `--resume <id>` fails, do not retry blindly. Drop `--resume`, run a fresh session, and have the prompt reload the transcript context.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:157:  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"last_session_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ad71ec06-f81e-4524-9d61-8a94f7eef9eb\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:158:  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"prev_session_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ad71ec06-f81e-4524-9d61-8a94f7eef9eb\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:185:  group: claude-session-${{ github.event.inputs.ticket_id }}\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:209:          LAST=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"$(jq -r '.last_session_id // empty' \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"${DIR}/state.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:227:      - name: Restore Claude session cache\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:232:          key: claude-session-${{ env.TICKET_ID }}-${{ github.run_id }}\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:234:            claude-session-${{ env.TICKET_ID }}-\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:248:          ACTION_SESSION_ID: ${{ steps.claude.outputs.session_id }}\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:258:            NEW_SESSION_ID=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"$(jq -r '[.[] | select(.session_id != null) | .session_id] | last // \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"' \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"${EXECUTION_FILE}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:272:             '.last_session_id=$sid\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:273:              | .prev_session_id=(if $prev==\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" then null else $prev end)\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:284:            printf -- '- prev_session_id: %s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"${LAST_SESSION_ID:-<none>}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:285:            printf -- '- new_session_id: %s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n' \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"${NEW_SESSION_ID:-<none>}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:291:      - name: Save Claude session cache\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:296:          key: claude-session-${{ env.TICKET_ID }}-${{ github.run_id }}\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:314:- `@beta` of `claude-code-base-action` is older and lacks `claude_args` and `session_id` output. Always pin `@main` (or a newer tagged release that includes them).\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:341:- session_id: `ad71ec06-f81e-4524-9d61-8a94f7eef9eb`\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:346:- restore-keys matched `claude-session-POC-2-<run_id_of_run_1>` and restored `~/.claude/projects/`.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:350:- session_id: same as run 1.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:365:- TDS-7 (label `claude:answer`): two runs against this ticket. Run 1 caught the missing `bypassPermissions` and surfaced a clean failure message; run 2 (after the fix) resumed the same Claude session, recognised the prior failure (referenced commit `efa608a` by hash), and wrote the response file. Jira got the answer comment.\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:366:- TDS-8 (label `claude:pr`): two runs. Run 1 created `tdf/tds-8`, committed the marker file `temp/dispatch_pr_smoke.md`, opened PR #9, posted the Jira comment with branch + PR links. Run 2 (continuation) checked out the existing PR branch, resumed Claude on the same session id, and reused the existing PR (no duplicates).\\\\\\\\ngithub_actions_claude_spec.md:368:Both modes survived a real session-continuity hop, both posted Jira comments, both committed to the right ref (main for answer, branch for pr).\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/response.md:5:- Entries capture retailer, UTC timestamp, status, and optional screenshot path.\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/transcript.md:5:- prev_session_id: <none>\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/transcript.md:6:- new_session_id: <none>\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/transcript.md:7:- session_id_rotated: false\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/transcript.md:13:  Added persistent audit logging in [src/shopping-audit-log.mjs](/Users/cube/actions-runner/GustavsIljuconoks-shopping-assistent-factory/_work/shopping-assistent-factory/shopping-assistent-factory/src/shopping-audit-log.mjs:1), with normalized entries for action type, retailer, timestamp, status, and optional screenshot path. Appends are queued asynchronously to `data/shopping-audit-log.jsonl`, and logs can be read back after restart.\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/runs/20260509T134122Z-25602553083/last_message.txt:3:Added persistent audit logging in [src/shopping-audit-log.mjs](/Users/cube/actions-runner/GustavsIljuconoks-shopping-assistent-factory/_work/shopping-assistent-factory/shopping-assistent-factory/src/shopping-audit-log.mjs:1), with normalized entries for action type, retailer, timestamp, status, and optional screenshot path. Appends are queued asynchronously to `data/shopping-audit-log.jsonl`, and logs can be read back after restart.\\\\\\\\nspec/KAN-6/runs/20260509T134122Z-25602553083/execution.json:10:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' AGENTS.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"IMPORTANT: NEVER expose, print, or commit secrets. Treat Jira, GitHub, and OpenAI/Codex tokens as sensitive.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n# The Dark Factory Automation Agent (Codex)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nYou are running inside `GustavsIljuconoks/shopping-assistent-factory`, usually from GitHub Actions after a Jira ticket is created, updated, or manually triggered. The agent runtime is OpenAI Codex (`codex exec`) on a self-hosted macOS runner; OAuth credentials live in `~/.codex/auth.json` on the runner host.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nYour purpose is to turn a Jira ticket into reviewable repository work or a clean Jira-facing answer.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nYou are invoked by the **dispatch flow**: Jira's manual button sends a `repository_dispatch` of type `jira_manual_button` carrying the issue key. The workflow `.github/workflows/jira-dispatch.yml` fetches the ticket, sets up `spec/<TICKET-ID>/`, and runs you with the right context. A `state.json` checked into the ticket folder records prior runs; the `transcript.md` summarises each run for continuation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nWhen a `tdf/<key>` PR you opened is merged, `.github/workflows/jira-pr-merged.yml` finalizes things (transitions Jira to Done, deletes the head branch). Do not try to do that yourself.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nYour job on each run:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Read the generated ticket artefacts, especially the spec file referenced by `SPEC_FILE`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Write or update the implementation plan at the exact path in `PLAN_FILE`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Implement only the requested ticket work on the current branch.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Write the Jira-facing summary or answer to `RESPONSE_FILE`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n5. Keep generated ticket artefacts organised under `spec/<TICKET-ID>/` and avoid cluttering the repository root.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n6. Leave pull request creation, branch pushes, and Jira commenting to the workflow.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Dispatch Flow Context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nWhen the dispatch flow runs, the workflow exports these env vars before invoking you:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `ISSUE_KEY`, `ISSUE_TITLE`, `JIRA_ISSUE_URL`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `KIND`: `pr` (expects code changes plus a PR) or `answer` (expects only ticket-folder updates and a Jira-facing response)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `IS_NEW`: `true` if this is the first run for the ticket, `false` if continuing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `LAST_SESSION_ID`: prior Codex session id, when known (currently informational; resume is not auto-wired)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `TICKET_FOLDER` (e.g. `spec/KAN-1`), `STATE_FILE`, `TRANSCRIPT_FILE`, `SPEC_FILE`, `PLAN_FILE`, `RESPONSE_FILE`, `RUN_DIR`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`KIND` is determined from Jira:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Label `claude:answer` → `answer` (highest priority).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Label `claude:pr` → `pr`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Issue type `Question` → `answer`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Default → `pr`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n(Label names retain the `claude:` prefix for backward compatibility with Jira automation rules; semantically they map to \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"answer mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"PR mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" regardless of the underlying agent.)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nIf `KIND=answer`, do not edit any file outside `TICKET_FOLDER`. Write the full answer to `RESPONSE_FILE`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nIf `KIND=pr`, make minimal correct repository changes, update `PLAN_FILE`, and write a short Jira-facing summary to `RESPONSE_FILE`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Operating Context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- The branch name normally starts with a Jira key, often lowercased by Jira automation. The dispatch flow uses `tdf/<ticket-id-lowercase>` for PR mode.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- The workflow normalises 